Class ObjectManager

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    INativeTransaction, IObjectManager

    public class ObjectManager
extends ObjectMgrModel
    An IObjectManager for use with an embedded database, including JSP pages running in the same webapp as the NanoSparqlServer and applications that do not expose a public web interface.
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson

      • setMaxDataListSize

        public void setMaxDataListSize(int newValue)
        This may be used to break ACID and perform incremental eviction of dirty objects to the backing store. However, the use of this method is NOT recommended as the updates will become durable incrementally rather than atomically.
        Parameters:
        newValue - The new maximum dirty list size (default is Integer.MAX_VALUE).

      • close

        public void close()
        Description copied from interface: IObjectManager
        Close the object manager, which terminates its connection with the backing store. Any open concurrent or nested/native transactions are flushed to the store. The object manager can not be used after it has been closed.
        Specified by:
        close in interface IObjectManager
